    "It is worth noting that poor and less reliable performance is observed when the number of trainings or layers is very small, as these designs do not fully function.",
    "Specifically, some inputs are not correctly converted, and their energy is lost due to scattering.",
    "Of interest, the loss related to spacing between each layer (Fig. 7b) shows a small dip around 10 mm and flattens out as the spacing increases.",
    "This discrepancy could be attributed to lower pixel utilization for shorter diffraction distances and larger losses due to scattering for larger diffraction distances.",
